0a%20payer%20platform%20to%20provide%20health%20plans%20with%20data%20aggregation%20capabilities%20for%20tasks%20like%20analytics%20and%20claims%20processing.%20Epic%20released%20its%20own%20payer%20platform%20in%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20March%2C%20Epic%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.beckershospitalreview.com%2Fehrs%2Fcarequality-releases-findings-in-epic-startup-dispute-12-notes.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efiled%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20formal%20dispute%20with%20Carequality%2C%20the%20data%20interoperability%20network%20that%20both%20Epic%20and%20Particle%20Health%20use%20to%20access%20and%20exchange%20patient%20information%20for%20their%20payer%20platforms.%20Epic%20alleged%20that%20some%20of%20Particle%20Health's%20customers%20were%20using%20Carequality%20to%20access%20patient%20data%20for%20non-treatment%20purposes%2C%20potentially%20violating%20HIPAA.%20The%20EHR%20company%20then%20cut%20off%20data%20requests%20from%20those%20Particle%20Health%20customers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20part%20of%20Carequality's%20review%20process%2C%20which%20reached%20a%20final%20resolution%20in%20October%2C%20Particle%20terminated%20its%20contracts%20with%20two%20of%20the%20customers%20in%20question%20and%20agreed%20to%20obtain%20written%20documentation%20from%20a%20third%20customer%20demonstrating%20appropriate%20use%20of%20Carequality's%20platform.%20Epic%20also%20agreed%20to%20revisit%20its%20own%20policies%20for%20determining%20whether%20an%20organization%20is%20using%20data%20for%20treatment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Particle's%20September%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dropbox.com%2Fscl%2Ffo%2F4ueymp83t2u10axccwi06%2FADU4CvpksDMPc1XZVt_wcww%3Fe%3D5%26preview%3D2024-09-23%2BParticle%2BHealth%2BComplaint.pdf%26rlkey%3Difg4iyhhy5sbv9xwofew7b2ug%26st%3Dhp4gxrht%26dl%3D0%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elawsuit%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20filed%20in%20the%20Southern%20District%20of%20New%20York%2C%20doubles%20back.%20The%20suit%20alleges%20that%20Epic%20used%20its%20