%20the%20citizenship%20of%20its%20parents.%20However%2C%20that%20will%20soon%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20going%20to%20have%20to%20get%20it%20changed%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr.%20Trump%20said%20in%20an%20interview.%20%26quot%3BWe'll%20maybe%20have%20to%20go%20back%20to%20the%20people.%20But%20we%20have%20to%20end%20it.%26quot%3B%20Although%20he%20had%20raised%20this%20issue%20during%20his%20first%20term%20as%20well%2C%20nothing%20substantial%20happened.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20the%20practice%20of%20every%20country%2C%20and%20Trump%20and%20his%20supporters%20have%20argued%20that%20the%20system%20is%20being%20abused%20and%20that%20there%20should%20be%20tougher%20standards%20for%20becoming%20an%20American%20citizen%2C%26quot%3B%20Russell%20A%20Stamets%2C%20Partner%20at%20Circle%20of%20Counsels%2C%20told%20Business%20Standard.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20right%20of%20birthright%20citizenship%20is%20based%20on%20the%2014th%20Amendment%20to%20the%20Constitution%20and%20is%20well-established%20under%20US%20law%2C%20so%20elimination%20would%20encounter%20significant%20legal%20challenges.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%2014th%20Amendment%20says%2C%20%26quot%3BAll%20persons%20born%20or%20naturalised%20in%20the%20United%20States%2C%20and%20subject%20to%20the%20jurisdiction%20thereof%2C%20are%20citizens%20of%20the%20United%20States%20and%20of%20the%20State%20wherein%20they%20reside.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump%20and%20other%20opponents%20of%20this%20policy%20say%20that%20this%20enables%20%26quot%3Bbirth%20tourism%26quot%3B%2C%20a%20phenomenon%20where%20pregnant%20women%20enter%20the%20US%20specifically%20to%20give%20birth%20in%20order%20for%20their%20children%20to%20have%20US%20citizenship%20before%20coming%20back%20to%20their%20home%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSimply%20crossing%20the%20border%20and%20having%20a%20child%20should%20not%20entitle%20anyone%20to%20citizenship%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Eric%20Ruark%2C%20director%20of%20research%20for%20NumbersUSA%2C%20which%20argues%20for%20reducing%20immigration%2C%20as%20per%20the%20Associated%20Press.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump%20also%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20want%20to%20be%20breaking%20up%20families%2C%20so%20the%20only%20way%20you%20don't%20break%20up%20the%20family%20is%20you%20keep%20them%20together%20and%20you%20have%20to%20send%20them%20all%20back%26quot%3B%2C%20which%20means%20legal%20citizens%20would%20also%20be%20expelled%20in%20order%20to%20keep%20families%20together.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%202011%20factsheet%20by%20the%20American%20Immigration%20Council%20says%20that%20removing%20birthright%20citizenship%20would%20affect%20everyone%2C%20and%20it%20will%20get%20difficult%20for%20American%20parents%20to%20prove%20citizenship%20of%20their%20children.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOur%20birth%20certificates%20are%20proof%20of%20our%20citizenship.%20If%20birthright%20citizenship%20were%20eliminated%2C%20US%20citizens%20could%20no%20longer%20use%20their%20birth%20certificates%20as%20proof%20of%20citizenship%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20factsheet%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Pew%20Research's%20analysis%20of%20the%202022%20US%20Census%2C%20about%204.8%20million%20Indian-Americans%20are%20living%20in%20America%2C%20of%20which%2034%20per%20cent%2C%20or%201.6%20million%2C%20were%20born%20in%20the%20country.%20These%20individuals%20are%20citizens%20of%20the%20United%20States%20under%20the%20current%20law.%20If%20Trump%20were%20to%20abolish%20this%20law%2C%201.6%20million%20Indians%20will%20be%20impacted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20president%20cannot%20amend%20the%20Constitution%20and%20an%20executive%20effort%20to%20restrict%20the%20right%20would%20amount%20to%20violation%20of%20the%2014th%20Amendment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20don't%20take%20his%20statements%20very%20seriously.%20He%20has%20been%20saying%20things%20like%20this%20for%20almost%20a%20decade%2C%26quot%3B%20Alex%20Nowrasteh%2C%20vice%20president%20at%20the%20pro-immigration%20Cato%20Institute%20told%20the%20Associated%20Press.%20%26quot%3BHe%20didn't%20do%20anything%20to%20further%20this%20agenda%20when%20he%20was%20president%20before.%26quot%3B%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1733853360000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-12%2Fo37c91h8_donald-trump-reuters_625x300_10_December_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fdonald-trump-to-eliminate-birthright-citizenship-its-impact-on-indians-7218980%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20United%20States%20grants%20citizenship%20to%20children%20born%20within%20its%20borders%2C%20regardless%20of%20the%20citizenship%20of%20its%20parents.%20However%2C%20that%20will%20soon%20change.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fdonald-trump-to-eliminate-birthright-citizenship-its-impact-on-indians-7218980%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Blackstone%20gets%20CCI%20nod%20to%20acquire%20stakes%20in%20two%20Bagmane%20Group%20entities%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1733852927000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fblackstone-gets-cci-nod-to-acquire-stakes-in-two-bagmane-group-entities-124121001348_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20proposed%20combination%20involves%20the%20acquisition%20of%20certain%20stake%20in%20the%20Bagmane%20Developers%20and%20Bagmane%20Rio%20(Target%20entities)%20by%20BREP%20Asia%20III%20India%20Holding%20Co%20VIII%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fblackstone-gets-cci-nod-to-acquire-stakes-in-two-bagmane-group-entities-124121001348_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Jamie%20Foxx%20reveals%20he%20had%20a%20stroke%20in%202023%22%2C%22conten